[thinking] I’m thinking about whether I need to assert `mkdirs` in the native environment if the parent directory exists, especially since this is about handling temp files for methods that may not exist. In Gradle, sometimes tests can reuse instances, while JUnit creates new temporary files. There could be an issue with `Files.copy` failing if the file already exists. I need to check the classpath in the JVM after certain class loading steps, ensuring everything runs correctly. It’s important to reflect on how these tests execute!
[thinking] 
